HEADWORD: Saururae
<hw>Sau*ru"rae</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr.
Gr. <?/ a lizard + <?/ a tail.]</ety> <fld>(Paleon.)</fld> <def>An
extinct order of birds having a long vertebrated tail with quills along
each side of it. Archaeopteryx is the type. See <er>Archaeopteryx</er>,
and <er>Odontornithes</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

